\b7NAME\c9
\tls - list directory contents

\b7SYNOPSIS\c9
\t\b7ls\c9 [\b5OPTION\c9]... [\b5FILE\c9]...

\b7DESCRIPTION\c9
\tList information about \b5FILE\c9s (the current directory by default.)  Sort entries alphabetically.

\t\b7-a\c9
\t\tdo not ignore entries starting with '.'.  Behaves identically to \b7-A\c9.

\t\b7--nocolor\c9
\t\tdisable colored output

\t\b7-l\c9
\t\tuse a long listing format

\t\b7-1\c9
\t\tlist one file per line

\t\b7--help\c9
\t\tdisplay this help and exit.

\tUsing color to distinguish file types is enabled unless \b7--nocolor\c9 is passed.  \b7ls\c9 emits color codes only when the standard output is connected to a terminal.  The \b7LS_COLORS\c9 environment variable can change color settings.

